This paper deals with optimal control and trajectory generation problems in robotics, which are typically studied in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses online trajectory optimization, which involves real-time processing of sensor data, and this is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY). The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques for communication channel estimation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses image processing techniques for robot sensing, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper uses the generalized Hopf formula, which is a numerical method for solving partial differential equations, and this falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
